  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The output, e.g., in a prediction task, is one of the inputs.",
    "Sutskever and Vinyals propose the application of RNNs to solve general sequenceto-sequence problems.",
    "The idea is to use one LSTM to read the input sequence, one timestep at a time, to obtain a large fixed dimensional vector representation, and then use another LSTM to extract the output sequence from that vector.",
    "The second LSTM is conditioned on the input sequence.",
    "(Sutskever et al., 2014) Sequences pose a challenge for NN because they require that the dimensionality of the inputs and outputs is known and fixed."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "(Sutskever et al., 2014) Sequences pose a challenge for NN because they require that the dimensionality of the inputs and outputs is known and fixed."
  ]
}